# Session 03 — Image-based surface + L2 estimation

Date: 2026-04-17

## Goal

Replace the feature-centroid-driven pia estimators of session 03 v2 with a
purely **image-intensity-driven** approach that also estimates the L2
boundary.  The algorithm must be distribution-driven (no hand-tuned absolute
thresholds) and generalise across HCR (multi-channel fluorescence) and CZ
(GFP confocal) volumes.

User-specified priors (biological / geometric, not calibration):

* Top of the volume is always blank (outside tissue).
* Pia (surface) lies within the top 25 % of the volume in z.
* Below pia lies L1 (neuropil); L2 is a second, deeper intensity jump.
* L2 is roughly parallel to pia.
* For CZ, L2 must be detected from *background* intensity only
  (segmentation-mask == 0), because GFP cell bodies dominate the raw
  profile and mask the underlying layer signal.

